---
description: MVC architecture conventions for the project
alwaysApply: true
---

Architecture rules:

The application follows a minimal MVC architecture.

Responsibilities:

Controllers
- Handle HTTP request data.
- Call services for business logic.
- Select the view to render.

Services
- Contain business logic.
- Must not generate HTML.

Views
- Generate HTML only.
- Must not access the database.

Routing
- Maps HTTP paths to controller actions.

Layout
- Responsible for rendering the page structure.
- Controllers pass logical view names only.
